## {{ rule.title }}

[26 U.S.C. § 56](https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/26/56) defines Alternative Minimum Taxable Income (AMTI) as regular taxable income plus the § 56 add-backs (state/local-tax itemized deduction, depreciation timing differences, ISO bargain element, NOL adjustments). [§ 55(b)(3)](https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/26/55) preserves the [§ 1(h)](https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/26/1) preferential rates on long-term capital gain and qualified dividends inside AMT, so AMTI is partitioned into ordinary AMTI and preferential AMTI for the tentative-minimum-tax computation downstream.

For 2025 the supported posture is a standard-deduction filer with no ISO bargain element, no accelerated depreciation, no private-activity-bond interest, and no itemized SALT; the loader at `tax_pipeline/y2025/us_inputs.py` rejects any non-zero preference item with a `NotImplementedError` (F-US-1). Under that posture AMTI equals taxable income; the preferential AMTI is the regular [§ 1(h)](https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/26/1) preferential capital base plus qualified dividends.

